div1.p: In the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division..
U. S v Ching Yow, U.S. Ching
In the matter of the application of Ng Key Tung, for a writ of Habeas Corpus. NO. 2897 Order to show cause.

Above named petitioner having made application to this Court for writ of habeas corpus by and through his father Get Tock addressed to the United States Commissioner of Immigration White, and to such persons or agents acting by, through or under them or in behalf of the U. S. Government, in whose custody the petitioner is shown by his petition to be confined and restrained of his liberty and to be ordered deported, as alleged in his petition illegally and unwarrented and without power, and not under virtue of or by authority of the Statutes of the United States, and the Court being fully advised, it is ordered thath the Honorable U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White, or such persons acting under or through said party and in behalf of the United States Government having custody of said petitioner Ching Hing, show cause, if any they have before this Court at the Court room at the Federal Building in the City of Seattle on the 5th day of November Dec, 1914, at 10 o'clock in the a M. why said application should not be granted, and in the meantime U. S. Commissioner of Immigration White, as well as said persons who are acting under and through you, refrain and desist from deporting or placing, and removing said petitioner Ng. Key Tung from said Court District or carrying into effect any warrant or order for hsi deportation which may be held by you.
